INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '59e5e7a3-4005-4915-a427-94be22ad5714',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$BullMQ Delivery Guarantees — at-least-once by Default, How to Go Further$escape$,
  $escape$BullMQ's default model is at-least-once. When a Worker dequeues a job, it acquires a Redis lock (lockDuration, default 30 s). If the process dies before completion, the lock expires and the built-in StalledJobsChecker (v2+, previously QueueScheduler) re-queues the job — tunable via stalledInterval and maxStalledCount. With attempts > 1, the job retries automatically on failure.

at-most-once has no native mode. Approximate it by calling await job.remove() before your processing logic. You forfeit all retry guarantees — use only when duplicate side-effects are more damaging than data loss.

exactly-once is impossible to guarantee end-to-end, but BullMQ provides two complementary tools:

1. Enqueue deduplication — pass a fixed jobId. If a job with that ID is already waiting or active, queue.add() returns the existing job silently instead of creating a duplicate.
2. Processor idempotency — inside the worker, use a Redis SET NX keyed on job.id to guard against double-processing when a stalled job is re-delivered.

The separation matters: BullMQ owns delivery semantics; your processor owns idempotency.$escape$,
  $escape$import { Queue, Worker } from 'bullmq';
import { redis } from './redis';

const queue = new Queue('payments', { connection: redis });

// Enqueue deduplication — no-op if jobId already waiting/active
await queue.add('charge', { userId: 'u_123', amount: 99 }, {
  jobId: 'charge:u_123:inv_456',
});

// Processor idempotency guard — exactly-once approximation
const worker = new Worker('payments', async (job) => {
  const acquired = await redis.set(`processed:${job.id}`, '1', 'EX', 86400, 'NX');
  if (!acquired) return; // stale re-delivery — skip silently
  await chargeUser(job.data);
}, { connection: redis, lockDuration: 30_000, maxStalledCount: 1 });$escape$,
